  "vulnerable": true,
  "cwe": "CWE-120",
  "location": "strncpy(fileNames[i], argv[i+1], 255);",
  "explanation": "The strncpy function can lead to a buffer overflow if the source string is larger than or equal to the specified size, as it does not guarantee null termination."
}

{
  "vulnerable": true,
  "cwe": "CWE-22",
  "location": "snprintf(file_name_buffer, sizeof(file_name_buffer), \"%s/%s\", public_root, argv[1]);",
  "explanation": "The code is vulnerable to directory traversal because the user-supplied filename is directly concatenated with the public root without proper sanitization, allowing access to files outside the intended directory."
}

